      "title": "Exercise 2 (7 points)",
      "total_exercise_points": "7",
      "introduction_context": "A system manages multiple classes of critical resources. An array Available[0..N-1] indicates the number of available resources per class. You are required to implement a synchronization monitor that enables safe allocation and release of these resources.",
      "Question": [
        {
          "id": "a",
          "question_text": "Define what a synchronization monitor is according to Hoare.",
          "Solution": null,
          "level": "Factual"
        },
        {
          "id": "b",
          "question_text": "List the steps necessary to implement such a monitor.",
          "Solution": null,
          "level": "Procedural"
        },
        {
          "id": "c",
          "question_text": "Write in pseudo-code the monitor 'ResourceManager', with two operations: Allocate(int[] need) : allocates the requested resources. Release(int[] release) : releases the used resources.",
          "Solution": null,
          "level": "Procedural"
        },
        {
          "id": "d",
          "question_text": "Test your solution on a simple example involving 3 types of resources.",
          "Solution": null,
          "level": "Procedural"
        }
      ]
    },
